HEADWORD: Opposability
<hw>Op*pos`a*bil"i*ty</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>The
condition or quality of being opposable.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>In no savage have I ever seen the slightest approach to
<qex>opposability</qex> of the great toe, which is the essential
distinguishing feature of apes.</q> <rj><qau>A. R.
Wallace.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Opposable</ent>⟦br⟧
